verbose_text: Investigating the causes of mitochondrial impairment in haploinsufficient mice, we found that while Eif6 +/- fibers have no change in copper-zinc superoxide dismutase (CuZn-SOD, SOD1) (XREF_FIG E), they have significantly higher level of manganese-superoxide dismutase (Mn-SOD, SOD2) compared to WT fibers (p < 0.04) (XREF_FIG F and XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY).
